cache_rw_type_description_raid_5	=	"RAID 5 requires at least three SSDs. This configuration has a better read performance than RAID 1 and provides fault tolerance. It can sustain one SSD failure without data loss. When an SSD fails, data from that SSD will be reconstructed from the parity striped across the remaining SSDs. As a result, both read and write performance will be severely impacted when RAID 5 is in a degraded state. RAID 5 is ideal when capacity and cost are more important than performance."
